<TITLE> RAB arrests 4 robbers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 11 (bdnews24.com)The Rapid Action Battalion (RAB) on Monday night arrested four robbers and seized arms from their possession at Savar in Dhaka. The robbers were arrested from Jhauchar village under Hemayetpur union when they were about to go on a robbery. The four have been identified as Badsha Mia alias Joydar, 30, Khairul Islam, 30, Atikur Rahman, 27, and Mainal Haque alias Rafiqul Islam, 36. Squadron leader Shah Mizan-ul-Haque, camp commander of RAB-4 in Savar, said that they were informed about a group of armed robbers preparing for a robbery. Acting on this information the RAB conducted a special operation and arrested the four robbers on Monday night, Haque added. He told bdnews24.com that they had seized two US-made revolvers, four rounds of ammunition for the revolvers and a sharp dagger from them. The robbers were handed over to the Savar Police Station on Tuesday noon. A case has been filed with the Savar Police. bdnew
